import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('date')['price'].mean().reset_index()
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data_grouped)
    plt.title('What is the average price of stocks over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    max_stock = data.loc[data['price'].idxmax()]
    sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data)
    plt.axhline(max_stock['price'], color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max Price: {max_stock['price']:.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("Which stock had the highest price in the given period?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
